sigillum (0.2.2-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Sign tab: explicit CAdES/PAdES/XAdES radio selector; PAdES is enabled
    only for `.pdf` sources, XAdES only for `.xml`, CAdES always available.
  * Sign / Decrypt: passwordless PKCS#12 files are accepted (only PKCS#11
    tokens still require a PIN; symmetric decrypt still requires the key).
  * Verify: report every signer on multi-signed CAdES and XAdES, including
    nested re-enveloping such as `name-signed-signed.p7m`.
  * Output filename for CAdES on an already-`.p7m` source no longer
    duplicates the extension.
  * New `sigillum extract` subcommand and GUI "Extract content…" button:
    recover the original document carried inside a `.p7m`, recursing
    through nested CMS layers automatically.
  * Bash and zsh shell completion scripts generated with shtab and
    installed alongside the binary.

 -- Danilo Abbasciano <danilo@piumalab.org>  Wed, 03 Jun 2026 10:00:00 +0200

sigillum (0.2.1-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * GUI keyboard shortcuts: Ctrl+Q / Ctrl+W to quit, Ctrl+1..6 to switch
    tab, Ctrl+, to open Settings.
  * Auto-detect PKCS#11 token: extra search directories configurable
    from Settings or via `config set --add-driver`, with a quick-add
    shortcut surfaced inside the "Missing token driver" popup.
  * Settings tab: prompt to save / discard / cancel when leaving with
    unsaved changes.
  * Document the OpenSC limitation on Italian CNS qualified signing
    certificates (Secure Messaging key embedded in vendor drivers, see
    upstream issue OpenSC#2782).
  * Project: published to PyPI; .deb/.rpm built and released via
    GitHub Actions on every `v*` tag.

 -- Danilo Abbasciano <danilo@piumalab.org>  Wed, 27 May 2026 15:00:00 +0200

sigillum (0.1.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial release.
  * Document signing:
    - PAdES (signed PDF) Level B and T
    - CAdES (.p7m enveloping) Level B and T
    - XAdES (enveloped XML) Level B and T
    - Visible PAdES signature with preset corner, optional logo and
      mouse-driven box selection on a PDF preview.
  * Document verification: separate checks for hash, signature, signer
    chain, timestamp and TSA chain. Manual chain walker for Italian
    qualified certificates lacking subjectAltName (required by
    cryptography.PolicyBuilder).
  * Standalone RFC 3161 timestamping: .tsr (detached evidence) and .tsd
    (ETSI TS 119 422 envelope with embedded content).
  * File encryption: symmetric with password (AES-256, AES-128, 3DES,
    Blowfish in CBC + PKCS#7 + PBKDF2-SHA256), asymmetric against the
    configured device, and asymmetric against an arbitrary PKCS#12
    recipient (CMS EnvelopedData .p7e).
  * Credentials:
    - PKCS#12 files
    - PKCS#11 hardware tokens (YubiKey via libykcs11, Bit4id
      Digital-DNA Key via libbit4xpki, OpenSC for generic
      smartcards/CNS/CIE)
    - Auto-detection of inserted tokens + compatible driver, with
      paths scanned in user homes for Aruba/InfoCamere/Dike installs.
  * Multi-country eIDAS support:
    - National Trust Lists for any EU/EEA member state are discovered
      dynamically via the EU LOTL (no hardcoded URLs).
    - Per-country PEM bundles under $XDG_DATA_HOME/sigillum/trusted/.
    - Primary country derived from $LANG, with explicit override and a
      list of additional countries to include in the verification
      trust store.
    - GUI panel in Settings: country dropdown, per-country refresh and
      remove buttons, "+ Add EU country" dialog.
    - CLI: tsl-import --country, tsl-list, config set
      --country/--active-countries.
  * TSL XMLDSig signature verification (ETSI TS 119 612) anchored to
    the EU LOTL, supporting RSA-PKCS1v15 and RSA-PSS/MGF1.
  * Background auto-refresh of the primary country's TSL at startup if
    missing or older than 30 days.
  * Full CLI mirroring every GUI operation: sign, verify, timestamp,
    encrypt, decrypt, tsl-import, tsl-list, detect, config, gui.
  * Settings persisted in ~/.config/sigillum/settings.json with mode
    0600 (carries optional TSA Basic-Auth password).
  * Italian translation (po/it.po, 100% coverage).
  * Bilingual man page sigillum(1) (English source, Italian via po4a).

 -- Danilo Abbasciano <danilo@piumalab.org>  Tue, 26 May 2026 09:00:00 +0200
